[Rearch] Migrate regression task #1 (#3420)

Move a couple things out of `utask_main` into `utask_preprocess` and
`utask_postprocess`, add a bunch of tests.

@jonathanmetzman PTAL. I would appreciate some guidance on the TODOs in
unit tests, specifically around how to set up the environment so that we
do not need to mock out so much code.

---------

Co-authored-by: jonathanmetzman <31354670+jonathanmetzman@users.noreply.github.com>
Update default build target for flashing Android Cuttlefish (#3450)

Adapt check bad builds (#3441)

Reland of https://github.com/google/clusterfuzz/pull/3416
So basically, what I changed is that we're now returning `False, True,
None` when `'BAD_BUILD_CHECK'` is not set. This leads
`update_build_metadata` to return early.

---------

Co-authored-by: jonathanmetzman
Compile proto
Fix error type renaming (#3464)

Issue Update Security Flow (Google Issue Tracker) (#3460)

In https://github.com/google/clusterfuzz/pull/3442 we added a save-issue
security flow. This PR tidies up and ensures that this flow also works
for updating an issue.

---------

Co-authored-by: Ravi Mistry <rmistry@google.com>

review.body:
Thanks for the context! I still do have some concerns with this approach:

- This is dependent on expand() being called at the right time, which makes it hard to reason about. 
- It's a destructive, irreversible transformation on the environment. 
- The implementation introduces a bit of complexity. 

Is there any possibility that CR_SOURCE_ROOT can be calculated at runtime by the fuzzer in some other way, e.g. based on the cwd() + argv[0] ? 

If there's no other way to do this, it may be still better to just hardcode the logic to set `CR_SOURCE_ROOT` in `build_manager.py` as a chrome-specific hardcode.

pull_request.title: Add environment variables expansion capability
pull_request.body: This is needed to get some path for Chrome that will depend on BUILD_DIR.

Speculative fix for #3429

Initial Public Implementation for Google Issue Tracker (#3369)

This is the first commit to add Google's issue_tracker as an option for
filing and updating bugs found by ClusterFuzz.

It seems to make sense to carry forward the pattern that we see with
Jira and Monorail, of having an __init__ file that contains Issue,
Action, and IssueTracker classes, backed by an IssueTrackerManager class
in a separate file, handling i/o.

This commit starts small, creating a new directory for issue_tracker and
including only __init__ with stubs for each of those classes we expect
to need.

Remove UAR stack size (#3427)

To be aligned with default settings.

Add the ability to create queues in project_setup (replaces #3306) (#3362)

A recently merged PR (https://github.com/google/clusterfuzz/pull/3322/)
refactored many of the original files on this initial feature (PR#3306)

Integrate with issuetracker public API + Some cleanup (#3433)

This PR contains the changes necessary to get ClusterFuzz working with
the issuetracker public API- It fixes the discovery URL and completes
the `client.build_http()` method.

The integration with public API was verified locally by using a GCP
service account and tested against a test component. Example created
issue: b/306010501
The steps taken to setup the local environment have been documented in
the `issue_tracker.py` file.

Cleanup has also been done-
* The `_override_priority_and_type` method has been removed. It was not
used.
* The `config`dict has been replaced by `component_id`. That was the
only field accessed from the `config` dict.
Register the new google_issue_tracker (#3436)

Get list of bad revisions instead of bad builds (#3435)

@jonathanmetzman Could you please take a look?

Rework centipede flag generation (#3419)

It is easier to manage constants for centipede arguments separately, so
that it's nicer to read and to comprehend.

This CL also extensively use FuzzerArguments object since it's been
made for handling fuzzing arguments nicely.

---------

Co-authored-by: jonathanmetzman <31354670+jonathanmetzman@users.noreply.github.com>

Rename uworker_output.error to uworker_output.error_type (#3440)

Co-authored-by: jonathanmetzman <31354670+jonathanmetzman@users.noreply.github.com>
Fix module import when remote processing module (#3447)

Add 'collaborators' Field to Issue (#3432)

This is a first step in creating a security workflow in Google Issue
Tracker that auto-assigns a collaborator to the issue.

Add Issue Access Limit to Issue Class as Private Data (#3437)

We will use this data in the subsequent PRs to allow saving and updating
an issue's access level

---------

Co-authored-by: jonathanmetzman <31354670+jonathanmetzman@users.noreply.github.com>
